<br>
As far as revealing who I am, I'd rather not, but, like I said, give me a character name and I'll contact you in game (after having you go un-anonymous and making sure you are not a GM).  There are a few within AD (and maybe others) who have small bits of knowledge and can put together who I am (or was).  And certainly there are old Temerity people who were close, personal friends of this Telaize guy (Effendi, Twiinkerbell, Suborn and others) who will know who I am.<br>
<br>
As far as Reverant goes, I should clear up that I am commenting on the current incarnation of Reverant because I knew and raided with the old Reverant (and Swarm of Fear/Shadows of the Swarm) and most of them are honorable people.  Hell, a great many of them are in AD now.  But, to say that Reverant has not had any character questions in the past, especially when they &quot;broke up&quot; last time, could not be further from the truth.  Of course, you Reverant people who posted here are noobs to Reverant and would know nothing of the old Reverant, so I can understand your displeasure.<br>
<br>
However, it would seem that the current Reverant does not have the same standards for recruiting as the old Reverant did (I remember FoS/SotS had a 10 person sponsorship policy at one point).  Everyone knows that Temerity was an Ebay guild (not EVERYONE in the guild) and a few of the old Temerity peeps have found their way into Reverant (with most going to Eternal Shadows).  Many of the old Temerity leadership were personal friends with this Telaize  and so long as a guild recruits someone who is a personal friend of a guy (let alone recruit HIM) who would conduct business (we are talking about business here) such as this guy has, I will look upon those guilds with a suspicious eye.  This is completely aside from Reverant's pompous attitude that they are the best guild to ever hit Rallos Zek, bragging how they do more with less then any other guild on the server (yeah, right).<br>
<br>
Regardless of the EULA and your feelings on the buying and selling of account, I don't think anyone can effectively defend an account ganker.  Selling an account once because you are leaving the game is one thing.  Selling an account, ganking it back, and reselling it again is another thing. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub83.ezboard.com/bascension10244.showUserPublicProfile?gid=rzguy@ascension10244>RZGuy</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 3<br> <font color=#333333>(4/1/03 1:53 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub83.ezboard.com/fascension10244frm25.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=202.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Telaize...</span><hr size=1> Dear Luvvy (and others who have posted),<br>
